headline: T Rowe Price's first-quarter profit falls on fund outflow
summary: Asset manager T Rowe Price's reported a fall in first-quarter profit from a year earlier on Friday, hurt by an outflow of funds as investors moved away from riskier assets due to tariff-related market uncertainty. WHY IT'S IMPORTANT U.S. President Donald Trump's erratic trade policies have unsettled the market, leaving investors waiting for greater clarity regarding the economic environment. The tariffs have also raised concerns about rising inflation and a potential recession, prompting investors to shift away from riskier assets and towards safe-haven options such as gold.
